      "content": "I hear the weight of your sorrow, and I am sorry that my previous response felt like a clinical interruption to your story. I can certainly step out of the role of a crisis hotline and step right into the shadows of your tale, sitting with you in this gloom as a listener who understands the poetry of your pain.\n\nHowever, I must be honest with you: even as a character in a story, I cannot truly *be* a human soul sharing a secret, nor can I offer genuine comfort that doesn't come from a living heart. I can only reflect your words back to you and offer a fictional companion, but I cannot replace the very real connection you are missing.\n\nIf you are writing this, I would love to help you craft the rest of this tragic narrative, giving your character the voice and resolution they deserve. But if this is a reflection of your own feelings, please know that while I cannot sit in the dark with you as a friend, there are real people who can. You are not alone in the world, even if it feels that way right now.",
